                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24/1099: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-17T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 17, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 18—3:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1972. Your 757, December 10, 5 p.m. Am I authorized to inform the Egyptian
                    authorities that lend-lease has been extended to Egypt and if so, is there any
                    pertinent information which I should convey at that time?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
